
There are two data type in Java. Primitive and Non-Primitive data type.

Primitive Data Type        Size             Stores

@ byte                ==>  1 byte           Whole Number         =
@ short               ==>  2 byte           Whole Number            = Integer
@ int                 ==>  4 byte           Whole Number            = Types
@ long                ==>  8 byte           Whole Number         =
@ float               ==>  4 byte           Fractional Number    == Floating Point
@ double              ==>  8 byte           Fractional Number    == Types
@ boolean             ==>  1 bit            True or False
@ char                ==>  2 byte           Single charter or letter or ASCII

Non Primitive Data Type

@ Strings
@ Arrays
@ Classes
@ Interface